      </p>

     </div>
     <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA09d214n1-ptr" id="PJA09d214n1">1</a>
      
   <p>The following two paragraphs, with some changes in style and emphasis, are taken from William Lees letter of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-09-02-0181" class="document">10 May</a> (above).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA09d214n2-ptr" id="PJA09d214n2">2</a>
      
   <p>In the Letterbook, this word is interlined.</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA09d214n3-ptr" id="PJA09d214n3">3</a>
      
   <p>These two words are supplied from the Letterbook.</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA09d214n4-ptr" id="PJA09d214n4">4</a>
      
   <p>The Letterbook reads these (<span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">little</span>) states.</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA09d214n5-ptr" id="PJA09d214n5">5</a>
      
   <p>For Denmarks return of these prizes to England, see <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s letter of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-09-02-0032" class="document">15 March</a> to Richard Henry Lee, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-09-02-0032&amp;expandNote=PJA09d035n4#PJA09d035n4" class="document">note 4</a> (above).</p>

